    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on exploiting park factors and soft-tossing matchups to buoy our offensive production. **Mickey Moniak** leads the charge as our top-ranked play with a 75.98 efficiency score, benefiting immensely from a massive 14% park boost and a favorable encounter with Sasaki. Similarly, **Corbin Carroll** remains an essential pivot point; despite facing a formidable arm in Gausman, his elevated 71.33 score is cemented by an elite xwOBA and the premium slotting of the #2 spot in the order. We are also leaning heavily into the wheels today, as **Brice Turang** and **Trevor Story** draw critical efficiency bumps (+4% each) due to their matchups against pitchers with high-delivery windows, which we project will yield prime stolen base opportunities\u2014a vital commodity for our Roto standing.\n\nThe primary bench dilemma today centered on **Alex Freeland**, who posted a respectable 52.07 but ultimately couldn't crack the threshold against the depth of our middle infield. While **Alex Freeland** benefited from a significant 14% park advantage, his #9 spot in the batting order proved to be a dealbreaker when compared to the reliable daily output of **Max Muncy**, who maintains a strong 61.16 score by leveraging a 7% platoon advantage against Schultz. Meanwhile, we are exercising extreme caution with **Jose Caballero**; his 52.65 score is precarious given he faces Ragans\u2014the toughest pitcher on our opponent docket today (2.52 xERA). Despite the 13% platoon boost, the risk of a sub-40 performance is high if he cannot navigate the elite arm, though we are keeping him in the lineup to hedge against potential late-game defensive versatility.",
